{
  "texts": [
    "Besides the self-designed spiking XOR problems, we also test our models on standard benchmarks.",
    "Spiking Heidelberg digits (SHD) and spiking speech command (SSC) datasets convert the original audio data into the spike format through a bionic inner ear model.",
    "SHD contains about 10,000 high-quality recordings of English and German speech for digits ranging from 0 to 9.",
    "A total of 12 speakers are included in the dataset, in which 6 are female and 6 are male.",
    "The speakers range in age from 21 to 56, with an average of 29 years old."
  ]
}